review:
I was impressed and suprise when Lego introduced a &quot;mecha&quot; theme, but its more closely akin to Exo Squad back in the day.  Though these are larger, they pretty much have the same idea ( increases firepower, strength, speed, overall capacity of a infantry solider).
Which is the reason why I bought this model. 

 However, for stealthy-ness it doesnt stand up.  White is a pretty bad color for that application.  As for flying the wings could be better.  But in the thought of flimsyness and sort it is a stealth/scout &quot;mech.&quot;
The Stickers arent that bad, but stickers on legos tend to last only one year anyways...

Weapons wise, the laser cannon is nice, the double edge sword is more of a pain, and only one rocket and one backup laser/maser emitter is weak.  But again its mainly for stealth and scouting.

The cockpit is flimsy also, wouldnt hold up even in pretend combat let alone lego &quot;combat.&quot;
